 invoke [ɪn'vok]
 	 //If you invoke a law, you state that you are taking a particular action because that law allows or tells you to.求助于 (法律) 
 	 --eg：The judge invoked an international law that protects refugees.  法官援用了一项保护难民的国际法律。

 	 // If you invoke something such as a principle, a saying, or a famous person, you refer to them in order to support your argument. 援引 

 	 --eg:economists who invoke the principle of "consumer sovereignty" to support their arguments. 
		援引“消费者主权”原则来支持自己论点的经济学家们。

	// If something such as a piece of music invokes a feeling or an image, it causes someone to have the feeling or to see the image. Many people consider this use to be incorrect because is the correct word for this. 使人想起 
	--eg：Appalachian Spring" by Aaron Copland invoked the atmosphere of the wide open spaces of the prairies. 艾伦·科普兰的《阿帕拉契亚的春天》使人想起了那种辽阔草原的氛围。

=============================================================
composite		[kɑm'pɑzɪt]
	// A composite object or item is made up of several different things, parts, or substances. 合成的 
	--eg：Galton devised a method of creating composite pictures in which the features of different faces were superimposed over one another. 高尔顿发明了一种将不同脸的部位相互叠加而创作合成图片的方法。

	//Composite is also a noun. 合成物
	--eg:Cuba is a composite of diverse traditions and people. 古巴是一个不同传统和民族的融合体。


==============================================================
legacy	 ['lɛgəsi]
	//A legacy is money or property which someone leaves to you when they die. 遗产 
	--eg：You could make a real difference to someone's life by leaving them a generous legacy. 
	你留给某人一大笔遗产就可以真正改变他的生活。
	// A legacy of an event or period of history is something which is a direct result of it and which continues to exist after it is over. 遗留问题 
	--eg:a programme to overcome the legacy of inequality and injustice created by Apartheid. 
	解决种族隔离引起的不平等和不公正等遗留问题的一个计划。

=============================================================